communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During 2013, Mongolia reported 3 outbreaks of FMD, serotype A, 2 in the Bayan-Ulgii province (in the western part of the country) and one in the Dornod province (the eastern part of the country). For background on these outbreaks, see commentaries in ProMED-mail archive numbers 20130927.1971578 and 20130711.1819287.

These 3 new outbreaks occurred in the province of Sukhbaatar, located in the eastern part of the country. This is the 2nd time that FMD serotype A has been reported in East Mongolia, following the outbreak reported in September 2013 in the Dornod province.

Sukhbaatar borders the People's Republic of China (Inner Mongolia province) to the south for 485 km, with Dornogovi province to the west for 165 km, with Khentii province to the north for 260 km, and with Dornod province to the north east for 430 km.

A map of the administrative divisions of Mongolia and another of Sukhbaatar province are available at http://www.ephotopix.com/mongolia_political_map.html and http://www.infomongolia.com/ct/ci/192/Sukhbaatar%20Aimag, respectively. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1J79.]
